# Supabase MCP Configuration

Implement the Supabase MCP connection using `mcp-remote` as a bridge to the remote SSE endpoint, passing the required Authorization header.

## Proposed Changes

### Configuration
#### [MODIFY] [mcp_config.json](file:///c:/Users/daria/.gemini/AXON/mcp_config.json)
- Add a new server entry `supabase`.
- Use `npx -y mcp-remote` command.
- Pass the Supabase MCP URL and Authorization header as arguments.
- Credentials will be extracted from the user's provided [supabase_mcp.json](file:///c:/Users/daria/.gemini/AXON/scratch/Dev/AXON-agents/shared-resources/mcp-configs/supabase_mcp.json).

